Package: GapProcedure
Type: Package
Title: Finds clusters of genetically similar DNA sequences using the Gap Procedure.
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Date: 2015-08-31
Authors@R: c(
    person("Irene", "Vrbik", email = "irene.vrbik@mcgill.ca", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("David", "Stephens", email = "d.stephens@math.mcgill.ca", role = "aut"))
Maintainer: Irene Vrbik <irene.vrbik@mcgill.ca>
Description: The Gap Procedure is a distance-based clustering algorithm for finding 
distinct groups among DNA sequence data.  Clusters assertained on the basis of gaps 
in sorted pairwise distances. 
